==English==
The Philippine Church Independente (Philippine Independent Church) also well-known as Church Aglipayan or simply Aglipayan, is a catholic tradition Church of native origin, that is to say, national and not governed by foreigners. It was founded on 1902 under the guide of the priest, lawyer and Philippine guerrilla Gregorio Aglipay as a national catholic church for the Philippines. The church was born along with independence of the nation of the Spanish Empire and it was developed  due to the ecclesiastical disadvantages that the one caused that the official catholic church (the Roman Catholic Church) entirely was dominated by Spanish elements. Gregorio Aglipay had been excommunicated by the Vatican in 1899, due to his militant commitment with the independence of his country. The Philippine Church Independente founded by him rejected the romanistas authority of the Roman Pope and doctrines, for that reason they arose current within the church that until rejected the doctrine on the Trinity, but in 1947 the church declared Trinitaria officially. The Philippine Church Independente counts today with approximately 2 million believers who are not only in the Philippines, but that also in present branches of this church in the United States and Canada. The Independent Philippine Church is a member of the Anglican Comunión and of the Union of Utrech of Old Catholic Churches, it consequently maintains relations of brotherhood with all the integral churches of those organizations.

